
[1]torrefy

   TOR'REFY, v.t. [L. torrefacio; L. torridus, torreo,and facio.]

   1. To dry by a fire.

   2. In metallurgy, to roast or scorch, as metallic ores.

   3. In pharmacy, to dry or parch, as drugs, on a metalline plate till
   they are friable, or are reduced to any state desired.
